<br>
1. Enchanting weapons was in enchanters' description when game came out. Adding a proc buff is just doing that, regardless of how you try to spin-doctor it.<br>
<br>
2. Wizards are not buffing class. Seriously, how many of you keep tank OKiel'd 100% of the time when there is no better damageshielder in group? Anyone? And if you don't why not? Why would you cast some proc buff, if you're not casting our current buffs?<br>
<br>
3. Knowing balance (and more precisely, SOE's vision of balance), the spell they would implement would be next to useless and then there would be tons of posts about how crappy they are. Just like there are tons of posts now about Al'Kabors and how crappy they are. Or the posts about MB, now that it fits SOE's vision of balance, there are tons of people whining about it.<br>
<br>
4. We are not buffing class. The SpellShield for example is in TOTALLY wrong spellbook. It should be enchanter spell, not a wizard spell. I've yet to meet any raiding 57+ wizard who is happy we have SpellShield.<br>
<br>
5. We're about direct damage, not indirect. O'Kiels didn't have upgrades for like the first 2 years and the only reason we originally had it was a mistake. It was supposed to be removed when EQ went live but some developer forgot it. Reverse/inverted damageshield, which proc buff would be, is not direct damage. Nor do wizards have DoT-type spells.<br>
<br>
6. We are not buffing class. For example the newest O'Kiels (PoP-era) is self only.<br>
<br>
7. The illusions that such buffs would bring group-friendliness to our class are so far fetched as can be. Currently we offer snare, roots (CC), ports, evacs, okiels, levitation, invis, spellshield in addition to our primary role... and if those aren't enough, I guess we need AE DT and haste, slow, mez and heals before some wizards would be happy with our group-friendliness.<br>
<br>
8. Druids and necros have lots more &quot;support-type&quot; spells in their spellbooks than we do, yet usually people tend to group druids and necros even less than wizards. So having support type spells isn't clearly something groups look for.<br>
<br>
9. We are not buffing class. There are tons of buffing classes out there already. Why blur class lines even further, as soon as we get buffs, we'll see enchanters getting proper nukes and shamans bypassing us in direct damage area. And that would be only fair... at that point mages should overnuke us with large margin, just for them to have even one niche to fill. Since it looks like wizards don't like that niche.<br>
<br>
10. DPS that's what we are wanted for in groups. We have wizards whining about mana being issue, then we have wizards posting that mana isn't issue, but being below tanks aggro is. So guys, which is it? Sounds like people want to have the cake and eat it too.<br>
<br>
As a tad bit of history, I've played wizard about 3 years and 47 weeks now. We've had our ups and downs, but never before Luclin have wizards shined like we shine now. Back before Kunark wizards owned, but not as well as we do now. Kunark started to tone casters down, Velious took it to the extreme, but Luclin returned us to glory. PoP returned us to even better situation. When you can chip over 10% off from a mob with single nuke (even without crits) and contribute easily a ton of damage to groups and raids, what more can you ask? World on a silver platter? Or is the problem that people have soloed to 60+ and are now at loss, when they have no friends?<br>
<br>
The problem isn't enchanters and clerics being more wanted than wizards, the problem is the number of clerics/enchanters compared to wizards. For every 65th wizard there seems to be 0.5 enchanters and even less clerics.<br>
<br>
Other problem is scared people. They won't group if there isn't cle/enc there. Last grouping I had, we had sk, sk, dru, brd, wiz, shm. No cleric, no enchanter. Yet we were exping in plane of water. I guess the n00bs of the game have taken lessons from dr00ds and only way to group effectively for them is to have war, cle, enc. The holy trinity is not needed. Druids and shamans really got beefed up in the patches and yes, they can heal now. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
SOE has learned their lessons, they will not create a class that would be perceived crucial like enc/cle are. The people who keep posting to wiz boards wanting people to perceive wizards as crucial are fooling themselves and would honestly be better off starting a cle/enc and enjoying that life. Because, after all, we all play the game for fun and if it is not fun, why do it? The game has what, 14 different classes to choose from, why try to blur the lines and change classes to match one other, why not just pick another class that seems to be better suited?<br>
<br>
-myz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artillis>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Enjoys Sheep Erotica</span><br>  Posts: 1769<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 1:06:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26302.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group-friendly wizard buff-like attack spells</span><hr size=1> Thank you for stating your opinion fully and clearly Myztic and on that note I think I can agree with most of what you said.<br>
