<br>
There is alot more to being &quot;group friendly&quot; than providing pretty little buff icons to your group.  Anyone that is familiar with our class looks to have them in the party when possible.  The problem is that most encounters necessitate a meat shield, a healer, a slower/debuffer, crowd control, and buffer/support class(es).  If these roles aren't completely necessary, they at least make the encounters much easier.  Wizards face alot of competition in the role of DPS-delivery, and in some low risk grouping situations you will find that we play second fiddle to a melee class in the public eye.  This leaves us with soloing or looking for friends to group with (which generally means an opportunity of engaging more dangerous content ANYWAYS).<br>
<br>
The only thing I would add for Wizards is MORE &quot;stun&quot; type spells.  At 63+ Telekin is a Godsend, but it would be excellent to have more means to stun or immobilize lvl 55+ mobs than the same old Magic Based resist type spells.  Having the ability to save healer mana, being able to burn down a mob quickly when necessary, and being able to evacuate and save the party are all key abilities that make us a powerful grouping class.  While we certainly have our share of worthless spells in our arsenal, our good spells are exceptional, and without question make us specialists in the area of delivering magical damage.<br>
<br>
I'd don't want to be &quot;group friendly&quot; to a bunch of unintelligent sods looking for a new buff whore.  I want to nuke shit down and save people's asses in a pinch. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=snyine>Snyine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 9:23:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26302.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group-friendly wizard buff-like attack spells</span><hr size=1> link the damage buff/weapon proc to a group familiar spell  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krela>Krela</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 9:25:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26302.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group-friendly wizard buff-like attack spells</span><hr size=1> I don't buff, I nuke.<br>
